s . The name is now in widespread and frequent use outside Wales, in many cases representing a transferred use of the surname so spelled, which is derived from the given name."]},{"name":"Rees","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of Welsh Rhys, in some cases representing a transferred use of the surname so spelled, which is derived from the Welsh given name."]}]},{"name":"Goch","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Italian <b>Rocco</b>; ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Iorwerth ap Einion ap Rhys Goch was born about 1140, in Flintshire, Wales, his father, Eonion ap Rhys Goch, was 22 and his mother, Rhys Goch, was 18. He married Sian ferch Dafydd Fychan ap Dafydd ap Ieuan ap Trahaearn ap Caradog about 1195, in Flintshire, Wales. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1140–":"umbes 1140–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1145–1210":"1145–1210","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1124–Female":"1124–Surnud","about 1140":"umbes 1140","about 1195":"umbes 1195","1124":"1124","1145":"1145","1210":"1210","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","Garthmyl, Aberriw, Mongomeryshire, Wales":"Garthmyl, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1140–":"noin 1140–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1145–1210":"1145–1210","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1124–Female":"1124–Kuollut","about 1140":"noin 1140","about 1195":"noin 1195","1124":"1124","1145":"1145","1210":"1210","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","Garthmyl, Aberriw, Mongomeryshire, Wales":"Garthmyl, Montgomeryshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales"},"fr":{"about 1140–":"environ 1140–Décédé","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1145–1210":"1145–1210","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","1120–Male":"1120–Décédé","1124–Female":"1124–Décédée","about 1140":"environ 1140","about 1195":"environ 1195","112